<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057110-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 3 and b = 5. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 3" class="text"/></p>
<p>
A = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1002" id="qn1002" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 3 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>5.8</li><li>31.0</li><li>59.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={3}^{{2}}+{5}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={9}+{25}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={34}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{34}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{5.8309518948453}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{5.8}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{3}}{{5}}\right)}}}\approx{30.963756532074}\approx{31}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{30.963756532074}^{\circ}\approx{59.036243467926}\approx{59}</m>.</p>

</solution>
